Package gold_miner

Class Board

java.lang.Object
gold_miner.Board
public class Board
extends java.lang.Object
Class implementing the board consisting of square tiles explored by the miner either rationally (as a smart agent) or randomly

Note that the row and column numbers in this class (as well as in all other classes responsible for the back-end behavior) are zero-based.

  • Field Summary

    Fields 
    Modifier and Type Field Description
    static char BEACON
    Character code for a beacon square tile, which returns the distance between this tile and the gold tile, provided that the gold tile is in one of its four cardinal directions and that there is no pit between this tile and the gold tile
    static char EMPTY
    Character code for an empty square tile, which is a regular tile with no special effects whatsoever
    static char GOLD
    Character code for the gold square tile, which results in a winning game-over situation should the miner step on this tile
    static char OUT_OF_BOUNDS
    Character code for an out-of-bounds square tile, which is a tile outside the dimensions of the board (the miner can scan this tile but cannot visit it)
    static char PIT
    Character code for a pit square tile, which results in a losing game-over situation should the miner step on this tile

    • beaconScan

      public int beaconScan​(Square beacon)
      Returns the distance between the given beacon and the gold square tile, provided that the gold tile is in one of its four cardinal directions and that there is no pit in between this tile and the gold tile

      This function assumes that the given square tile is a beacon.

      Parameters:
      beacon - beacon whose distance from the gold square tile is returned
      Returns:
      distance of the given beacon from the gold square tile, subject to the conditions explained
